      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Project Summary -**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FJNUwmbgGyua"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "This project focuses on analyzing customer financial and credit behavior using the Paisabazaar dataset containing 100,000 customer records and 28 features. The dataset includes information related to income, loans, debts, payment behavior, credit utilization, banking details, and credit scores.\n",
        "\n",
        "The main objective of this project is to perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), data cleaning, data visualization, and understand the factors affecting customer credit scores.\n",
        "\n",
        "Several preprocessing techniques were applied, including:Removing unnecessary columns, Handling invalid values, Treating unrealistic age values\n",
        "Handling outliers using the IQR method.\n",
        "Different univariate, bivariate, and multivariate charts were created to analyze relationships between variables such as income, debt, payment behavior, occupation, and credit score etc.\n",
        "\n",
        "The project helps identify high-risk and financially stable customers, enabling better credit risk analysis, customer segmentation, and business decision-making."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "F6v_1wHtG2nS"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Problem Statement**\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yQaldy8SH6Dl"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Financial institutions manage large amounts of customer financial and credit data. Understanding customer behavior is important for reducing financial risk and improving lending decisions.\n",
        "\n",
        "Customers differ in income, debt, repayment behavior, credit utilization, and loan history. Poor analysis of these factors can lead to loan defaults, delayed payments, and financial losses.\n",
        "\n",
        "This project aims to analyze customer financial data using Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) and visualization techniques to identify patterns affecting credit scores and customer financial stability."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DpeJGUA3kjGy"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### **Define Your Business Objective?**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PH-0ReGfmX4f"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "- Analyze customer financial and credit behavior.\n",
        "- Identify high-risk customers with poor repayment patterns and high debt.\n",
        "- Improve credit risk management and reduce loan default risk.\n",
        "- Segment customers based on income, occupation, payment behavior, and credit score.\n",
        "- Support better loan approval and financial product decisions.\n",
        "- Understand relationships between key financial variables like income, debt, and credit utilization.\n",
        "- Improve business profitability by reducing financial risk and targeting suitable customers."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PhDvGCAqmjP1"
      }
    },
