        " Upon examining the variables in our dataset, we found that they consist of\n",
        " three data types: integer, float, and object (string). Each variable serves\n",
        " a distinct purpose in understanding customer financial and credit behavior.\n",
        "\n",
        "- 'ID' for the unique record identifier,\n",
        "- 'Customer_ID' for the unique customer identifier,\n",
        "- 'Month' for the monthly record of the customer,\n",
        "- 'Name' for the customer’s name,\n",
        "- 'Age' for the age of the customer,\n",
        "- 'SSN' for the customer’s social security number or identity number,\n",
        "- 'Occupation' for the profession/job role of the customer,\n",
        "- 'Annual_Income' for the yearly income earned by the customer,\n",
        "- 'Monthly_Inhand_Salary' for the monthly salary received after deductions,\n",
        "- 'Num_Bank_Accounts' for the number of bank accounts owned,\n",
        "- 'Num_Credit_Card' for the number of credit cards held,\n",
        "- 'Interest_Rate' for the interest rate applicable to loans/credits,\n",
        "- 'Num_of_Loan' for the total number of loans taken,\n",
        "- 'Type_of_Loan' for the category/type of loans,\n",
        "- 'Delay_from_due_date' for the number of delayed payment days,\n",
        "- 'Num_of_Delayed_Payment' for the total delayed payments made,\n",
        "- 'Changed_Credit_Limit' for changes in the customer’s credit limit,\n",
        "- 'Num_Credit_Inquiries' for the number of credit inquiries made,\n",
        "- 'Credit_Mix' for the quality/type of credit maintained,\n",
        "- 'Outstanding_Debt' for the remaining unpaid debt amount,\n",
        "- 'Credit_Utilization_Ratio' for the ratio of credit usage,\n",
        "- 'Credit_History_Age' for the duration of credit history,\n",
        "- 'Payment_of_Min_Amount' for whether the minimum payment was made,\n",
        "- 'Total_EMI_per_month' for the monthly EMI amount paid,\n",
        "- 'Amount_invested_monthly' for the monthly investment amount,\n",
        "- 'Payment_Behaviour' for the customer’s spending and payment pattern,\n",
